plot: As the team heads to Paris on a mission connected to Amir's undercover past, things get more personal.

The team moves to Paris, having got French secret service fiat, when Amir gets a somewhat cryptic call for help from Mina Bayoud, whose father he knew undercover in Algeria, that her brother Asim is about to detonate soon a bomb belt to avert Jihadist threat to their family. Although time lacks for proper preparation, Amir insists to 'return' in his undercover persona. The ISIS cell boss Omar Galloul respects him, but Asim doesn't want to abandon and Amir spots material for at least a second, bigger bombing. A failed French intervention makes Dalton loose track, and time runs out to trace Galloul's surviving deputy Jabir Fergani .—KGF Vissers
